nagers%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20nonbanks%2C%20shadow%20banks%2C%20or%20alternative%20asset%20managers%20%E2%80%94%20is%20an%20increasingly%20common%20way%20to%20borrow%20cash.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraditional%20lenders%2C%20including%20Bank%20of%20America%20and%20Wells%20Fargo%2C%20have%20pulled%20back%20on%20issuing%20loans%20to%20companies%20since%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20when%20new%20regulations%20required%20banks%20to%20hold%20more%20capital%20on%20their%20balance%20sheets%20to%20guard%20against%20loan%20losses.%20But%20businesses%20will%20always%20need%20to%20borrow%20cash%20to%20run.%20Investment%20firms%20such%20as%20Blackstone%2C%20The%20Carlyle%20Group%2C%20Apollo%20Global%20Management%2C%20and%20Ares%20Capital%20Corp.%20have%20pushed%20aggressively%20into%20the%20private-debt%20market%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20that%20need.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20smart%20bet%20for%20money%20managers.%20PitchBook%20data%20shows%20that%20private-debt%20funds%20returned%204.2%25%20last%20year%20as%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20lost%2018%25%20and%20investment-grade%20corporate%20bonds%20lost%20nearly%2016%25.%20A%20Morningstar%20index%20used%20as%20a%20proxy%20for%20private%20debt%20is%20now%20on%20track%20for%20its%20best%20year%20since%20the%20Great%20Recession.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20many%20thousands%20of%20companies%20taking%20on%20private%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20bank%20loans%20or%20issuing%20corporate%20bonds%20%E2%80%94%20are%20setting%20private-equity%20firms%20up%20to%20be%20more%20powerful%20than%20ever.%20The%20%241.75%20trillion%20market%20often%20charges%20companies%20higher%20interest%20rates%20than%20they%20might%20get%20at%20a%20bank%20because%20the%20firms%20take%20on%20risks%20that%20banks%20can't%20or%20won't.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20is%20that%20for%20a%20bank%20to%20write%20these%20loans%2C%20they%20have%20a%20significant%20capital%20cost%2C%26quot%3B%20Sean%20McKee%2C%20a%20national%20practice%20leader%20at%20KPMG%20who%20advises%20asset%20managers%2C%20said.%20He%20said%20that%20banks%20wouldn't%20stop%20lending%20to%20middle-market%20companies%20entirely%2C%20but%20they'd%20been%20exiting%20the%20space%20and%20focusing%20more%20on%20bread-and-butter%20services%2C%20including%20mortgages%2C%20credit%20cards%2C%20and%20auto%20loans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestment%20firms%20are%20eating%20into%20banks'%20long-held%20position%20as%20the%20main%20source%20businesses%20tap%20for%20cash.%20It's%20a%20staggering%20shift%20in%20who%20holds%20the%20power%20to%20lend%20to%20companies%20and%20make%20money%20on%20lucrative%20interest%20payments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate-credit%20managers'%20funds%20and%20their%20big%20institutional%20investors%2C%20such%20as%20pension%20funds%2C%20are%20intertwined%20with%20the%20successes%20and%20failures%20of%20more%20and%20more%20companies%3B%20companies%20often%20pay%20up%20for%20access%20to%20loans%20they%20might%20not%20otherwise%20get%20with%20traditional%20lenders.%20Managers%20say%20they're%20helping%20support%20the%20economy%2C%20offering%20businesses%20much-needed%20capital.%20Because%20of%20fewer%20regulations%2C%20direct%20lenders%20can%20also%20customize%20the%20sizes%20and%20terms%20of%20their%20loans%20in%20ways%20banks%20can't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20as%20expensive%20interest%20payments%20to%20private-investment%20firms%20weigh%20down%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20businesses%20across%20industries%20and%20as%20funds%20must%20deal%20with%20problems%20in%20their%20portfolios%2C%20some%20analysts%20and%20executives%20say%20a%20growing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-shadow-banking-silicon-valley-bank-collapse-lending-2023-3%5C%22%3Eshadow-banking%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20poses%20risks%20to%20the%20wider%20economy.%20Weaker%20companies%20would%20ultimately%20impact%20investors%20in%20those%20pension%20funds%2C%20endowments%2C%20and%20other%20big%20pools%20of%20capital.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Gockowski%2C%20a%20senior%20manager%20at%20Casey%20Quirk%2C%20Deloitte's%20investment-management%20consulting%20practice%2C%20said%20that%20despite%20low%20defaults%2C%20rising%20rates%20could%20leave%20unprepared%20companies%20vulnerable.%20%26quot%3BThat%20may%20get%20to%20unmanageable%20levels%20in%20some%20areas%2C%20which%20could%20lead%20to%20defaults%20and%20ultimately%20losses%20in%20the%20portfolios%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20private%20debt%20has%20interest%20rates%20that%20move%20in%20concert%20with%20benchmark%20rates%2C%20climbing%20rapidly%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20a%20win%20for%20lenders%20that%20can%20morph%20into%20pressure%20for%20some%20borrowers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pullback%20from%20commercial%20banks%20and%20the%20tighter%20credit%20conditions%20have%20opened%20up%20that%20opportunity%20even%20more%20significantly%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Tim%20Warrick%2C%20the%20group%20head%20of%20alternative%20credit%20at%20Principal%20Financial%20Group's%20%24507%20billion%20asset-management%20arm%2C%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarrick%2C%20whose%20team%20oversees%20%2410%20billion%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-toast-of-the-town-greenwich-economic-forum-2023-10%5C%22%3Eprivate-credit%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20focuses%20primarily%20on%20the%20lower-middle%20market%2C%20said%20companies%20getting%20financed%20today%20are%20in%20more%20stable%20industries%20such%20as%20software%20and%20parts%20of%20healthcare%20that%20offer%20steady%20cash%20flows.%20Like%20other%20investors%2C%20he%20also%20favors%20companies%20under%20the%20umbrella%20of%20%26quot%3B'break-and-fix'%20business%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20plumbing%20and%20electrical%20services%20that%20are%20consistently%20in%20demand%20and%20have%20reliable%20customer%20bases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20resilient%20businesses%2C%20such%20as%20software%20companies%20that%20sell%20their%20platforms%20to%20other%20companies%20and%20groups%20rather%20than%20to%20consumers%2C%20are%20the%20ones%20getting%20funded%2C%20rather%20than%20those%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20economic%20cycles%2C%20Spyro%20Alexopoulos%2C%20the%20cohead%20of%20direct%20lending%20at%20the%20private-credit%20manager%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-debt-direct-lending-golub-leveraged-finance-david-golub-2022-1%5C%22%3EGolub%20Capital%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20economy%20and%20the%20performance%20of%20our%20underlying%20borrowers%20have%20been%20very%20strong%20%E2%80%94%20actually%2C%20surprisingly%20strong%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20there's%20still%20discomfort%20around%20where%20the%20consumer%20is%20headed%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexopoulos%20said.%20Golub%20has%20experts%20on%20staff%20who%20specialize%20in%20helping%20companies%20in%20financial%20trouble%2C%20but%20right%20now%2C%20they're%20underused.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20prepared%20for%20worse%2C%20earlier%2C%20and%20we%20haven't%20seen%20it%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20may%20have%20to%20do%20with%20the%20type%20of%20portfolio%20that%20we've%20been%20curating%20versus%20others.%20But%20thus%20far%2C%20we%20haven't%20seen%20the%20stress.%20We%20would%20expect%20some%20at%20some%20point.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate-debt%20managers%20say%20they%20oversee%20strong%20underwriting%20standards%20and%20due%20diligence%20on%20companies%20before%20committing%20capital%20%E2%80%94%20the%20basis%20for%20any%20prudent%20debt%20investment.%20That's%20doing%20little%20to%20convince%20critics%20that%20the%20risks%20of%20private%20debt's%20rapid%20growth%20to%20companies%2C%20funds%2C%20and%20their%20investors%20are%20under%20control.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrzej%20Skiba%2C%20the%20head%20of%20US%20fixed%20income%20at%20RBC%20Global%20Asset%20Management%2C%20warned%20of%20floating-rate-debt%20concerns%20in%20a%20July%20report%3A%20%26quot%3BFunding%20costs%20are%20crippling%20to%20private-debt%20portfolio%20companies.%26quot%3B%20In%20May%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fpublications%2Ffiles%2Ffinancial-stability-report-20230508.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Federal%20Reserve%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20financial-stability%20risks%20private-credit%20funds%20pose%20were%20limited%20but%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20sector%20remains%20opaque%26quot%3B%20and%20assessing%20default%20risks%20is%20difficult.%20Colm%20Kelleher%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20board%20of%20the%20financial%20manager%20UBS%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Facc692c8-011b-4580-834b-64d1b9612f94%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20during%20a%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%20that%20he%20was%20concerned%20about%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20private%20markets%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20and%20that%20the%20next%20financial%20crisis%20would%20likely%20be%20in%20the%20shadow-banking%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20providers%20and%20asset%20managers%20still%20expect%20the%20global%20debt%20market's%20growth%20to%20multiply.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackrock-high-stakes-bet-private-credit-bdc-2023-10%5C%22%3EBlackRock%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20world's%20largest%20asset%20manager%2C%20which%20has%20expanded%20its%20private-credit%20platform%2C%20projects%20the%20global%20market%20will%20hit%20%243.5%20trillion%20by%202028.%20Outside%20financial%20services%2C%20those%20growth%20expectations%20have%20led%20to%20new%20business%20for%20other%20areas%2C%20such%20as%20the%20legal%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20law%20firms%2C%20including%20Ropes%20%26amp%3B%20Gray%20and%20Proskauer%2C%20have%20been%20adding%20lawyers%20focused%20on%20advising%20private%20funds%20to%20their%20practices.%20Lawyers%20such%20as%20Proskauer's%20Justin%20Breen%20have%20been%20among%20the%20go-to%20attorneys%20in%20the%20private-credit%20space.%20Breen%2C%20who%20advises%20clients%20including%20Ares%2C%20Bain%20Capital%2C%20and%20Churchill%20Asset%20Management%2C%20leads%20Proskauer's%20global%20finance%20practice%20and%20focuses%20primarily%20on%20counseling%20private-credit%20managers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20in%20the%20business%20of%20negotiating%20loans%20outside%20the%20banking%20system.%20The%20private-capital%20lobby%2C%20which%20has%20long%20advocated%20for%20private-equity%20managers%2C%20wants%20to%20keep%20it%20that%20way%20for%20their%20members'%20growing%20private-credit%20arms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20fall%2C%20the%20industry's%20main%20US%20trade%20association%2C%20the%20American%20Investment%20Council%2C%20released%20two%20reports%20advocating%20for%20private-credit%20managers%20and%20sent%20them%20to%20journalists.%20Drew%20Maloney%2C%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%20power%20broker%20who%20has%20been%20the%20group's%20president%20and%20chief%20executive%20since%202018%2C%20said%20in%20one%20of%20the%20reports%20that%20private-credit%20firms%20had%20%26quot%3Bdramatically%20increased%20the%20chances%20for%20struggling%20companies%20to%20get%20back%20on%20their%20feet%26quot%3B%20because%20of%20the%20firms'%20ability%20to%20take%20on%20more%20risks%20and%20work%20together%20with%20borrowers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilwood%20Hobbs%2C%20the%20head%20of%20sourcing%20and%20origination%20at%20Oaktree%20Capital%20Management%2C%20said%20some%20borrowers%20would%20struggle%20with%20increasingly%20expensive%20debt%2C%20especially%20those%20that%20borrowed%20when%20rates%20were%20much%20lower.%20%26quot%3BThis%20creates%20a%20lot%20of%20strong%20opportunities%20for%20private-credit%20providers%20without%20legacy%20portfolio%20issues%20to%20step%20in%20and%20support%20performing%20businesses%20navigating%20a%20more%20challenging%20economic%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirms%20often%20say%20that%20they%20have%20the%20advantage%20of%20working%20closely%20with%20portfolio%20companies%20if%20trouble%20hits%20and%20borrowers%20can't%20make%20payments.%20Denis%20Rudnev%2C%20a%20director%20at%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%20Ratings%2C%20said%20that%20during%20the%20volatility%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20lenders%20have%20offered%20borrowers%20temporary%20relief%20if%20they%20need%20it%2C%20such%20as%20amending%20or%20extending%20loans%2C%20using%20so-called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-11-02%2Fprivate-equity-pays-buyout-loans-with-more-debt-to-save-cash%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epayment-in-kind%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-11-02%2Fprivate-equity-pays-buyout-loans-with-more-debt-to-save-cash%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest%3C%2Fa%3E%20arrangements%2C%20or%20waiving%20certain%20conditions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20more%20of%20that%20now%2C%20but%20those%20types%20of%20strategies%20haven't%20really%20been%20tested%20in%20a%20prolonged%20higher%20rate%20environment.%20The%20duration%20of%20elevated%20interest%20rates%20will%20be%20a%20key%20focus%2C%20especially%20for%20this%20segment%20of%20the%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Rudnev%20said.%20In%20November%2C%20his%20team%20published%20a%20report%20stress-testing%202%2C000%20middle-market%20companies%20with%20private-debt%20financing%20and%20found%20that%20while%20default%20rates%20remained%20low%2C%20companies'%20credit%20metrics%20such%20as%20cash%20flow%20and%20liquidity%20could%20reach%20%26quot%3Bprecarious%20levels%26quot%3B%20under%20moderate-%20or%20severe-stress%20scenarios.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirms%20say%20they%20make%20ample%20information%20about%20their%20private-credit%20funds%20publicly%20available%20so%20investors%20can%20see%20whether%20the%20investments%20are%20appealing.%20Entities%20known%20as%20business-development%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20a%20common%2C%20tax-advantaged%20way%20for%20firms%20to%20offer%20private-credit%20investments%20%E2%80%94%20must%20file%20public%20disclosures%20with%20regulators.%20Publicly%20traded%20business-development%20companies'%20management%20teams%20hold%20earnings%20calls%20with%20Wall%20Street%20analysts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20regulators%20say%20private-credit%20funds%20manage%20five%20times%20the%20assets%20as%20business-development%20companies%20do%2C%20and%20the%20information%20they%20must%20disclose%20only%20goes%20so%20far.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20said%20in%20its%20financial-stability%20report%20in%20May%20that%20comprehensive%20data%20on%20the%20terms%20of%20private-credit%20deals%20and%20borrowers%20%26quot%3Bare%20lacking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-lenders-middle-market-deals-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701956720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656f7ff90ec98e92f74c5339%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-lenders-middle-market-deals-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20rush%20of%20businesses%20taking%20loans%20from%20private-equity%20firms%2C%20concerns%20about%20an%20opaque%20market%2C%20and%20a%20PR%20blitz%3A%20Shadow%20banking%20is%20going%20mainstream.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rungarino%40businessinsider.com%20(Rebecca%20Ungarino)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-lenders-middle-market-deals-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20com