5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6571a8d97a3c8094d5da86ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Attorney%20General%20Merrick%20Garland%20speaking%20during%20a%20press%20conference%20at%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20on%20December%206%2C%202023%2C%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFour%20Russian%20soldiers%20were%20indicted%20for%20war%20crimes%20against%20a%20US%20national%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20threatened%20to%20kill%20the%20man%20and%20did%20a%20%26quot%3Bmock%20execution%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20court%20records.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20the%20first%20such%20charge%20brought%20by%20the%20DOJ%2C%20according%20to%20Attorney%20General%20Merrick%20Garland.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJustice%20Department%20prosecutors%20have%20brought%20war%20crime%20charges%20against%20four%20Russians%20accused%20of%20torturing%20and%20performing%20a%20mock%20execution%20on%20an%20American%20civilian%20in%20occupied%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuren%20Mkrtchyan%20and%20Dmitry%20Budnik%2C%20two%20commanding%20officers%20of%20Russian%20military%20units%2C%20and%20two%20lower-ranking%20soldiers%2C%20identified%20by%20their%20first%20names%20Valerii%20and%20Nazar%2C%20were%20charged%20with%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20war%20crimes%2C%20unlawful%20confinement%20of%20a%20protected%20person%2C%20torture%2C%20and%20inhuman%20treatment%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fmedia%2F1327486%2Fdl%3Finline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecourt%20records%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nine-page%20indictment%2C%20issued%20by%20a%20grand%20jury%20in%20the%20Eastern%20District%20of%20Virginia%2C%20accused%20the%20soldiers%20of%20breaking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fgenocideprevention%2Fdocuments%2Fatrocity-crimes%2FDoc.33_GC-IV-EN.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EArticle%20147%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Geneva%20Convention%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.law.cornell.edu%2Fuscode%2Ftext%2F18%2F2441%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520act%2520of%2520a%2520person%2520who%252C%2520having%2520knowingly%2520seized%2520or%2Cexplicit%2520or%2520implicit%2520condition%2520for%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUS%20war%20crime%20laws%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20abduction%20of%20the%20unnamed%20American%20on%20April%202%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMkrtchyan%2C%20Valerii%2C%20and%20Nazar%20threw%20the%20victim%20%26quot%3Bface%20down%20to%20the%20ground%20while%20he%20was%20naked%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btied%20his%20hands%20behind%20his%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20before%20%26quot%3Bpointing%20a%20gun%20at%20his%20head%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbeating%20him%20with%20their%20feet%2C%20their%20fists%2C%20and%20the%20stocks%20of%20their%20guns%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20proceeded%20to%20%26quot%3Bforcibly%26quot%3B%20transport%20him%20to%20buildings%20that%20were%20being%20used%20as%20a%20military%20compound%2C%20where%20the%20man%20was%20severely%20beaten%20on%20his%20legs%2C%20back%2C%20stomach%2C%20and%20head%2C%20according%20to%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20victim%20was%20subjected%20to%20at%20least%20two%20interrogations%2C%20in%20which%20Mkrtchyan%2C%20Valerii%2C%20and%20Nazar%20inflicted%20%26quot%3Bsevere%20and%20serious%20physical%20and%20mental%20pain%20and%20sufferings%26quot%3B%20on%20him%2C%20the%20indictment%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBudnik%20also%20asked%20the%20man%20for%20his%20last%20words%2C%20per%20court%20records.%20Nazar%20and%20others%20then%20conducted%20a%20%26quot%3Bmock%20execution%2C%26quot%3B%20forcing%20him%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20%26quot%3Bputting%20a%20gun%20to%20his%20back%2C%20moving%20the%20position%20of%20the%20gun%2C%20and%20pulling%20the%20trigger%2C%20causing%20the%20bullet%20to%20go%20past%20the%20victim's%20head%20and%20causing%20him%20to%20believe%20he%20was%20about%20to%20die%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20indictment%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20indictment%2C%20the%20man%20was%20also%20forced%20to%20perform%20manual%20labor%20like%20digging%20trenches%20for%2010%20days%20while%20detained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20charges%20are%20the%20first%20of%20their%20kind%20to%20be%20brought%20by%20the%20Justice%20Department%2C%20Attorney%20General%20Merrick%20B.%20Garland%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fpr%2Ffour-russia-affiliated-military-personnel-charged-war-crimes-connection-russias-invasion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estatement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Justice%20Department%20will%20work%20for%20as%20long%20as%20it%20takes%20to%20pursue%20accountability%20and%20justice%20for%20Russia's%20war%20of%20aggression%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Ukrainian%20Prosecutor%20General%20Andriy%20Kostin%2C%20Russia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2F18%2Fukraine-russia-war-crimes-00127936%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20committed%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%20100%2C000%20alleged%20war%20crimes%20since%20the%20start%20of%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%20in%20February%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ficc-cements-putin-pariah-arrest-warrant-russia-war-crimes-ukraine-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eissued%20arrest%20warrants%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20Maria%20Alekseyevna%20Lvova-Belova%2C%20Russia's%20commissioner%20for%20children's%20rights%2C%20for%20their%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20the%20deportation%20of%20children%20from%20occupied%20areas%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoj-charges-russia-soldiers-w