20well-intentioned%20but%20misleading%2C%20both%20on%20facts%20and%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20his%20four%20arguments%20to%20substantiate%20his%20claim%20%E2%80%93%20that%20%E2%80%9CBJP%E2%80%99s%20victory%20is%20not%20so%20big%2C%20and%20Congress%20fall%20is%20not%20so%20deep%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20suffer%20from%20selective%20facts%20and%20subjective%20interpretation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20responses%20to%20the%20election%20results%20from%20the%20progressive%20camp%20are%20as%20surprising%20as%20the%20results.%20Some%20scholars%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fprogressives-stop-hectoring-india-parties%5C%22%3EPushparaj%20Deshpande%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20calling%20for%20self-censorship%20in%20publicly%20criticising%20Congress%20over%20its%20lacunae%20and%20acting%20as%20social%20evangelicals%20among%20the%20traditional%20vote%20base%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20providing%20the%20last%20mile%20connectivity%20that%20the%20Congress%20lacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-assembly-elections-hat-trick-2024%5C%22%3EThe%20Myth%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Hat-Trick%20and%20What%20the%20Statistics%20Really%20Say%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20like%20Yadavs%20are%20ignoring%20the%20political%20and%20ideological%20inefficacy%20of%20the%20Congress%20as%20an%20electoral%20opposition%20to%20the%20BJP.%20Both%20these%20approaches%20might%20provide%20false%20comfort%20to%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20secular%20camp%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20however%2C%20they%20help%20the%20onward%20march%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20juggernaut.%20This%20is%20why%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20reading%20of%20the%20election%20results%20demands%20close%20scrutiny.%20Let%20us%20dissect%20them%20one%20by%20one.%3Cu%3E%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20the%20Congress%20gain%209%20lakh%20more%20votes%2C%20or%2050%20lakh%20less%20than%20the%20BJP%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20bid%20to%20boost%20the%20morale%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20those%20opposed%20to%20Hindutva%20politics%2C%20Yadav%20observes%20that%20the%20total%20number%20of%20votes%20that%20the%20Congress%20polled%20against%20BJP%20in%20the%20four%20states%20should%20bring%20solace.%20All%20the%20votes%20the%20Congress%20procured%20in%20the%20four%20states%2C%20namely%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Telangana%2C%20worked%20out%20to%20be%204.9%20crore%20whereas%20the%20BJP%20got%20only%204.81%20crore.%20Hence%20the%20analysis%20that%20despite%20Congress%20losing%20three%20states%2C%20its%20vote%20share%20is%20higher%20by%209%20lakh%20than%20the%20BJP.%20Thus%2C%20the%20conclusion%20is%20that%20people%20still%20prefer%20Congress%20though%20it%20lost%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20mathematically%20correct%20but%20politically%20incorrect%20conclusion.%20It%20is%20for%20a%20simple%20reason%20that%20it%20includes%20Telangana%20in%20its%20overall%20vote%20calculation%20along%20with%20the%20three%20Hindi%20states.%20In%20Telangana%2C%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20fight%20was%20primarily%20against%20the%20Bharat%20Rasthra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%2C%20not%20the%20BJP.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20Telangana%20in%20the%20overall%20calculation%20completely%20glosses%20over%20the%20dismal%20performance%20of%20Congress%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27132111%2FThe-Wire-91.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27132111%2FThe-Wire-91.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27132111%2FThe-Wire-91-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27132111%2FThe-Wire-91-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686533%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECongress%20leaders%20Mallu%20Bhatti%20Vikramarka%2C%20Revanth%20Reddy%2C%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20among%20others.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40INCIndia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20exclude%20Telangana%2C%20the%20number%20of%20votes%20the%20Congress%20obtained%20in%20the%20three%20Hindi%20states%20is%203%2C98%2C42%2C%20115%20while%20the%20BJP%20polled%204%2C48%2C%2075%2C%20952.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20the%20BJP%20procured%2050%20lakh%20votes%20more%20than%20the%20Congress%20from%20these%20three%20states.%20However%2C%20if%20we%20include%20Telangana%2C%20the%20picture%20changes%20and%20hence%20provides%20false%20comfort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-bharat-rashtra-samithi-congress-kcr%5C%22%3EIn%20Telangana%2C%20Five%20Trends%20Highlight%20Divides%2C%20Gains%2C%20Losses%20and%20Blows%20to%20Expansion%20Plans%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20compare%20the%20same%20with%20the%202018%20elections%2C%20the%20predicament%20of%20the%20Congress%20becomes%20more%20stark.%20In%20the%20previous%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20obtained%203.41%20crore%20votes%20from%20these%20three%20states%20and%20Congress%203.57%20crore%20votes.%20Thus%20compared%20to%202018%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20tally%20rose%20by%201%20crore.%20The%20Congress%20could%20increase%20its%20tally%20by%20only%2047%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Developing%20Societies%20(CSDS)%20survey%20and%20the%20earlier%20Axis%20survey%20suggest%20that%20most%20of%20these%20new%20BJP%20voters%20happen%20to%20be%20from%20the%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%20and%20even%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs).%20This%20means%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20social%20base%20is%20eroding%2C%20further%20giving%20way%20to%20the%20BJP.%20This%20is%20a%20dangerous%20portent%20and%20would%20never%20be%20acknowledged%20if%20one%20takes%20comfort%20in%20misleading%20figure%C2%A0%209%20lakh%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20clubbing%20Telangana%20with%20the%20three%20heartland%20states%20and%20concluding%20that%20Congress%20got%209%20lakh%20more%20votes%20than%20the%20BJP%20will%20prevent%20the%20Congress%20from%20identifying%20the%20steep%20slide%20caused%20due%20to%20its%20chronic%20and%20organic%20ideological%20compromise%20with%20Hindutva%20in%20these%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20Telangana%2C%20Yadav%20seems%20to%20be%20enamoured%20by%20the%20resurgence%20of%20the%20Congress%20vote%20share%20from%2028%25%20in%20the%202018%20election%20to%2039.4%25%20in%202023.%20Though%20this%20resurgence%20is%20positive%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%20it%20did%20not%20deter%20the%20double-digit%20growth%20rate%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20factor%20should%20not%20be%20missed%2C%20because%20it%20leads%20to%20false%20comfort%20that%20the%20South%20has%20closed%20its%20door%20to%20the%20BJP.%20In%20Telangana%2C%20the%20BJP%20procured%206.9%25%20votes%20and%2014.43%20lakh%20votes%20in%20the%202018%20elections.%20But%20in%202023%2C%20it%20doubled%20to%2013.90%25%20with%2032.51%20lakh%20votes.%20It%20has%20not%20only%20increased%20its%20seat%20share%20from%20one%20to%20eight%20but%20also%20stood%20second%20in%20more%20than%2018%20constituencies%20where%20it%20deployed%20nefarious%20tactics%20of%20communal%20polarisation.%20Thus%2C%20the%20growth%20rate%20of%20the%20BJP%20has%20doubled%20and%20its%20vote%20share%20is%20already%20a%20third%20of%20the%20victorious%20Congress%2C%20which%20is%20a%20dangerous%20portent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20it%20has%20a%20consolidated%20vote%20share%20of%2036%25%20in%20spite%20of%20its%20electoral%20defeat.%20One%20should%20also%20not%20close%20their%20eyes%20to%20the%20noise%20it%20is%20making%20in%20Dravidian%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20the%20growing%20number%20of%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20shakhas%20in%20communist%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20the%20vote%20share%20of%20Congress%20sufficient%20to%20stage%20a%20comeback%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20strange%20logic%20that%20Yadav%20offers%20is%20that%20since%20the%20difference%20in%20vote%20share%20between%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20is%20hardly%202%25%20to%204%25%2C%20one%20need%20not%20worry%20much%20about%20the%20loss%20of%20power.%20Since%20the%20Congress%20has%20reattained%20a%20vote%20share%20of%2040%25%2C%20it%20would%20be%20easy%20to%20stage%20a%20comeback.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%20it%20is%20a%20mathematically%20correct%20but%20politically%20incorrect%20assessment%20of%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20situation%20in%20these%20three%20states.%20All%20of%20them%20are%20more%20or%20less%20bipolar%20states%2C%20with%20scarce%20influence%20of%20a%20third%20actor.%20These%20elections%20have%20shown%20that%20even%20the%20Dalit%2C%20Adivasi%2C%20and%20OBC%20social%20bases%20of%20smaller%20parties%20have%20been%20encroached%20on%20by%20the%20BJP.%20In%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20stagnation%20of%20vote%20share%20is%20an%20indication%20that%20it%20is%20not%20only%20an%20electoral%20decline%20but%20a%20political%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym-300x194.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym-1024x662.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684198%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22776%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBJP%20supporters%20hold%20up%20Modi%20posters.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20analyses%20of%20vote%20shares%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20in%20the%20past%20five%20elections%20in%20these%20three%20states%2C%20barring%20Chhattisgarh%20in%202018%2C%20show%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20is%20growing%20whereas%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20is%20either%20stagnating%20or%20declining%20with%20one%20or%20two%20exceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20an%20average%20of%2039.88%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2045.17%25%20in%202013.%20Whereas%20the%20Congress%20shows%20an%20average%20of%2037.14%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2040.64%25%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20average%20is%2042.96%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2048.45%25%20in%202023.%20The%20Congress%20shows%20an%20average%20of%2036.42%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2041.35%25%20in%202018.%20In%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20an%20average%20of%2040.10%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2046.27%25%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%20in%20bipolar%20elections%2C%20the%20Congress%20tends%20to%20lose%20its%20social%20base%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20is%20obvious%20in%20these%20elections%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20even%20though%20theoretically%20a%2040%25%20vote%20share%20is%20enough%20to%20stage%20a%20comeback%2C%20the%20increasing%20loss%20of%20its%20social%20base%20to%20the%20BJP%20makes%20it%20impractical.%20The%20reason%20for%20this%20lies%20in%20the%20opportunist%2C%20Hindutva%2C%20and%20neoliberal%20politics%20of%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthree-things-bjps-definitive-victory-in-the-assembly-elections-tells-us%5C%22%3EThree%20Things%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Definitive%20Victory%20in%20the%20Assembly%20Elections%20Tells%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20these%20results%20have%20no%20impact%20on%202024%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Yadav%2C%20in%202003%2C%20even%20though%20the%20BJP%20won%20in%20the%20very%20same%20states%2C%20it%20lost%20the%202004%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20and%20while%20it%20lost%20these%20states%20in%202018%2C%20it%20won%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20Hence%20one%20cannot%20extrapolate%20these%20results%20to%20have%20a%20bearing%20on%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20Again%20it%20is%20only%20a%20logically%20correct%20statement%2C%20but%20a%20historically%20and%20politically%20problematic%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20advent%20of%20Hindutva%20and%20the%20communal%20polarisation%20of%20society%20and%20its%20intensification%20during%20the%20Modi%20regime%2C%20the%20RSS-BJP%20has%20cultivated%20an%20unchallenged%20Hindutva%20appeal%20among%20the%20Hindu%20electorate%20cutting%20across%20caste%2C%20community%2C%20class%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh.jpg%201500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh-300x156.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh-768x400.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh-1024x533.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-255956%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22781%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECredit%3A%20RSS%20website%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RSS-BJP%20machinery%20has%20been%20creating%20false%20anxiety%20about%20the%20growing%20threat%20to%20the%20nation%20and%20Dharma%20which%20could%20only%20be%20thwarted%20by%20a%20%3Cem%3Evirat%20purush%3C%2Fem%3E%20like%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20of%20late%2C%20the%20elections%20have%20not%20become%20transactional%20affairs%20between%20the%20voter%20and%20the%20party%2C%20but%20they%20are%20becoming%20ideological%2C%20especially%20between%20the%20BJP%20voters%20and%20the%20party.%20Thus%2C%20whatever%20may%20be%20the%20results%20in%20the%20state%20elections%2C%20at%20least%20from%202013%2C%20the%20people%20of%20these%20three%20states%2C%20and%20those%20in%20the%20Hindi%20belt%20in%20general%2C%20have%20been%20overwhelmingly%20elected%20the%20BJP%20both%20in%202014%20and%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20results%20will%20definitely%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20neighbouring%20Hindi%20states%2C%20which%20together%20account%20for%20240%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20%E2%80%98Modi%20magic%E2%80%99%20but%20the%20colossal%20political%20failure%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20opposition%20in%20offering%20themselves%20as%20a%20credible%20alternative.%20Hence%20ridiculing%20this%20sad%20phenomenon%20as%20%E2%80%98impossible%20magic%E2%80%99%20is%20neither%20a%20serious%20analysis%20nor%20a%20serious%20critique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20the%20BJP%20lose%2019%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20if%20the%20same%20pattern%20repeats%20in%202024%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Yadav%2C%20if%20the%20same%20pattern%20of%20voting%20is%20repeated%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20the%20BJP%20would%20lose%2019%20seats%20and%20Congress%20would%20gain%2022%20seats.%20For%20such%20a%20thing%20to%20happen%2C%20the%20Congress%20should%20ensure%20that%20it%20repeats%20the%20same%20performance%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20for%20example%20the%202019%20elections.%20Rajasthan%20has%2025%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%2C%20Congress%20got%20more%20votes%20and%20seats%20in%20the%202018%20assembly%20elections%2C%20but%20could%20not%20win%20even%20one%20seat%20there.%20All%2025%20went%20to%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA).%20In%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20where%20the%20Congress%20got%2010%25%20more%20votes%20than%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%202018%20assembly%20elections%2C%20it%20could%20win%20only%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20%E2%80%93%20the%20BJP%20got%20the%20remaining%20nine.%20In%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20Congress%20won%20only%20one%20and%20the%20rest%2028%20were%20won%20by%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMere%20extrapolation%20of%20votes%20provides%20only%20mathematical%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20and%20politics%20of%20these%20states%20demand%20introspection%20and%20rupture%20with%20the%20past%20by%20the%20Congress%20to%20stage%20a%20comeback.%20But%2C%20the%20Congress%20party%20has%20not%20shown%20any%20inclination%20or%20a%20rupture%20from%20its%20soft%20Hindutva%20and%20neoliberal%20politics%20either%20in%20its%20campaign%20or%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20situation%2C%20Congress%20looks%20like%20a%20party%20with%20the%20same%20fibre%20as%20the%20BJP%20but%20with%20a%20different%20colour.%20Without%20a%20radical%20transformation%20of%20Congress%20politically%2C%20ideologically%20and%20organisationally%2C%20leave%20alone%20defeating%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20survival%20of%20the%20Congress%20itself%20would%20become%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20warning%20the%20party%20and%20nation%20about%20this%20possibility%20would%20be%20a%20disservice%20to%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%2C%20as%20a%20social%20activist%20engaged%20in%20anti-fascist%20battles%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20have%20always%20shared%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20dreams%20respectfully%2C%20though%20not%20his%20shifting%20political%20strategies.%20But%20this%20analysis%20took%20me%20by%20surprise%20and%20disbelief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Gramsci%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPessimism%20of%20the%20intellect%20and%20optimism%20of%20the%20will%E2%80%9D%20is%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20in%20these%20times%20of%20gloom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fshivasundar%5C%22%3EShivasundar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20activist%20and%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20based%20in%20Bangalore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701950437000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F11%2FModi-Shah.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdebate-yogendra-yadav-analysis-bjp-wins-assembly-polls-misleading%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Yadav%20had%20written%20that%20'BJP's%20victory%20is%20not%20so%20big%2C%20and%20Congress%20fall%20is%20not%20so%20deep'.%20Such%20a%20view%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20false%20comfort.%20If%20the%20Congress%20does%20not%20honestly%20address%20the%20issues%20it%20is%20facing%2C%20putting%20up%20a%20good%20fight%20in%202024%20will%20be%20extremely%20difficult.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdebate-yogendra-yadav-analysis-bjp-wins-assembly-polls-misleading%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Former%20French%20President%20Fran%C3%A7ois%20Hollande%20Joins%20Voice%20Cast%20of%20%E2%80%98Silex%20%26amp%3B%20the%20City%E2%80%99%20Animated%20Movie%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701950297000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2FSilex_Illustration_Cave.png%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235825482%22%2C