timesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fjammu%2Fseveral-feared-dead-after-vehicle-falls-into-gorge-at-zojila-pass-in-ladakh-jammu-kashmir-ganderbal%2Farticleshow%2F105814668.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%20four%20people%20are%20feared%20dead%20after%20the%20vehicle%20they%20were%20travelling%20in%20rolled%20down%20a%20deep%20gorge%20at%20Zojila%20Pass%20in%20Ganderbal%20district%20in%20Union%20Territory%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20on%20Thursday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Poorna%20Swami%E2%80%99s%20Translation%20of%20the%20Poem%20%E2%80%98Falasteeni%E2%80%99%20Awarded%20the%202023%20Jawad%20Memorial%20Prize%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07170656%2Fimage-1582.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%202023%20edition%20of%20the%20Jawad%20Memorial%20Prize%20for%20Urdu-English%20Translation%20has%20been%20awarded%20to%20Poorna%20Swami%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20the%20poem%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EFalasteeni%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(%E2%80%98Palestinian%E2%80%99)%20by%20Fehmida%20Riaz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20runner-up%20prize%20has%20been%20awarded%20to%20Mohd%20Aqib%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EPabandi%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(%E2%80%98Prohibition%E2%80%99)%20by%20Ahmed%20Nadim%20Qasmi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20poem%20%E2%80%98Palestinian%E2%80%99%20translated%20its%20source%20material%20with%20fidelity%2C%20but%20without%20sacrificing%20a%20poetic%20sensibility%20of%20its%20own.%20Among%20the%20poems%20we%20examined%2C%20it%20presented%20a%20shining%20example%20of%20how%20good%20translation%20threads%20the%20needle%20between%20minimising%20the%20loss%20of%20original%20metaphor%20and%20maximising%20the%20lyrical%20quality%20of%20the%20output%20language.%20The%20quality%20of%20submitted%20translations%20was%20consistently%20good%2C%20making%20for%20a%20tough%20choice%20but%2C%20ultimately%2C%20this%20poem%20truly%20stood%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20runner-up%2C%20%E2%80%98Prohibition%2C%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20short%20poem%20and%20the%20translator%20has%20effectively%20communicated%20its%20resistance%20against%20censorship%20and%20prohibition.%20The%20jury%20found%20the%20poem%E2%80%99s%20imagery%20of%20rolling%20pearls%20and%20drops%20falling%20on%20raging%20fires%20most%20evocative%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoorna%20Swami%E2%80%99s%20essays%20and%20reportage%20have%20appeared%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%2C%20Open%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ELondon%20Review%20of%20Books%3C%2Fem%3E%20(web)%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%20holding%20the%20position%20of%20India%20editor-at-large%20at%20the%20international%20translation%20quarterly%20%3Cem%3EAsymptote%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Swami%20also%20co-edited%20the%20journal%E2%80%99s%20first%20feature%20on%20Indian%20language%20poetry%20translated%20into%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20she%20is%20pursuing%20her%20PhD%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20South%20Asian%20Studies%20at%20Harvard%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohd%20Aqib%20is%20a%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20junior%20research%20fellow%20and%20a%20PhD%20candidate%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20English%20at%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fmirza-ghalib-temple-lamp-maaz-bin-bilal-review%5C%22%3E%20A%20Translation%20of%20Ghalib%E2%80%99s%20Persian%20Ode%20to%20Banaras%20Reminds%20Us%20of%20What%20Makes%20Us%20Hindustani%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Jawad%20Memorial%20Prize%20gets%20its%20name%20from%20Ali%20Jawad%20Zaidi%2C%20an%20Urdu%20poet%20and%20scholar%20and%20winner%20of%20several%20awards%20including%20the%20Padma%20Shri%2C%20the%20Ghalib%20award%2C%20Mir%20Anis%20award%20among%20others.%20The%20Prize%20was%20initiated%20shortly%20after%20his%20birth%20centenary%20in%202016%20to%20honour%20his%20legacy%20of%20literature%20that%20served%20as%20a%20bridge%20between%20languages%2C%20cultures%20and%20histories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20several%20books%20of%20prose%20and%20poetry%2C%20Zaidi%20published%20several%20scholarly%20works%20such%20as%20A%20History%20of%20Urdu%20Literature%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20ke%20Marsiyago%20and%20Taarikh-e-Mushayara%2C%20all%20of%20which%20contributed%20to%20his%20tireless%20efforts%20towards%20making%20Urdu%20literature%20accessible%20to%20all%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20language%20they%20speak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20for%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20prize%20were%20literary%20critic%20and%20translator%20Anisur%20Rahman%20as%20well%20as%20author%20Raza%20Mir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormerly%20a%20professor%20of%20English%20at%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%2C%20and%20a%20senior%20advisor%20at%20Rekhta%20Foundation%2C%20Rahman%20has%20worked%20and%20published%20in%20the%20areas%20of%20comparative%2C%20translation%2C%20postcolonial%2C%20and%20Urdu%20studies.%20His%20recent%20publications%20include%20%3Cem%3EEarthenware%3A%20Sixty%20Poems%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Rubric%20Publishing%2C%202018)%2C%20%3Cem%3EIn%20Translation%3A%20Positions%20and%20Paradigms%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Orient%20Blackswan%2C%202019)%2C%20%3Cem%3ESocioliterary%20Cultures%20in%20South%20Asia%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Niyogi%20Books%2C%202019)%2C%20%3Cem%3EHazaaron%20Khwahishein%20Aisi%3A%20The%20Wonderful%20World%20of%20Urdu%20Ghazals%3C%2Fem%3E%20(HarperCollins%2C%202019)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EHazaar%20Rang%20Shaairi%3A%20The%20Wonderful%20World%20of%20the%20Urdu%20Nazm%3C%2Fem%3E%20(HarperCollins%202022).%20Rahman%20has%20been%20a%20Shastri%20Fellow%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alberta%2C%20Canada%20(2001-2002)%20and%20a%20Visiting%20Scholar%20at%20Purdue%20University%2C%20US%20(2007).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaza%20Mir%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20William%20Paterson%20University%20in%20the%20US.%20His%20latest%20books%20are%20%3Cem%3EIqbal%3A%20Poet%20of%20the%20East%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Penguin%2C%202022)%20and%20%3Cem%3EMurder%20at%20the%20Mushaira%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Aleph%202021).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwhen-the-moon-gets-caught-in-the-barbed-wire-over-the-prison-wall-varavara-rao-poetry%5C%22%3EWhen%20the%20Moon%20Gets%20Caught%20in%20the%20Barbed%20Wire%2C%20Over%20the%20Prison%20Wall%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrevious%20winners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202022%20prize%20went%20to%20Sana%20R.%20Chaudhry%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EPyaare%20Ustaad%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20written%20by%20Julien%20Columeau.%20The%20runner-up%20prize%20was%20shared%20by%20Shama%20Askari%20for%20her%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98Begum%E2%80%99%20by%20Ibn%20e%20Sai%E2%80%99d%3B%20and%20Sabyn%20Javeri%20for%20%E2%80%98The%20Busy%20Woman%2C%E2%80%99%20a%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EMasroof%20Aurat%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20by%20Khalida%20Hussain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202021%20prize%20was%20shared%20by%20Aalim%20Akhtar%20for%20his%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHari%20Bol%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20by%20Zakia%20Mashhadi%2C%20and%20Bilal%20Tanweer%20for%20%E2%80%98Parasite%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3EKeera%3C%2Fem%3E)%20written%20by%20Bilal%20Hasan%20Minto.%20There%20was%20a%20jury%20commendation%20for%20Nazia%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EChhottam%20Jaan%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%20by%20Zeenath%20Sajida%20and%20Fathima%20M.%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98Shadows%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3ESaaye%3C%2Fem%3E)%20by%20Khalid%20Jawed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202020%20winner%20was%20Haider%20Shahbaz%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Sea%E2%80%99%20by%20Khalida%20Hussain.%20There%20was%20no%20runner-up.%20However%2C%20there%20was%20a%20jury