d%20at%20all%20costs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGuterres%20invoked%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20he%20took%20office%20in%202017%2C%20Article%2099%20of%20the%20UN%20Charter.%20This%20states%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Secretary-General%20may%20bring%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Security%20Council%20any%20matter%20which%20in%20his%20opinion%20may%20threaten%20the%20maintenance%20of%20international%20peace%20and%20security.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20focused%20in%20particular%20on%20the%20difficulties%20in%20delivering%20aid%20and%20providing%20health%20care%20to%20people%20in%20the%20enclave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20current%20conditions%20are%20making%20it%20impossible%20for%20meaningful%20humanitarian%20operations%20to%20be%20conducted%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnowhere%20is%20safe%20in%20Gaza.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20pushed%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20humanitarian%20cease-fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20a%20humanitarian%20cease-fire%2C%20the%20means%20of%20survival%20can%20be%20restored%2C%20and%20humanitarian%20assistance%20can%20be%20delivered%20in%20a%20safe%20and%20timely%20manner%20across%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%E2%80%9D%20Guterres%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Security%20Council%2C%20currently%20chaired%20by%20Ecuador%2C%20has%20held%20several%20sessions%20on%20the%20conflict%20in%20Gaza%20since%20Hamas%20group%E2%80%99s%20October%207%20attacks%20in%20Israel%20that%20killed%201%2C200%20people%20with%20240%20more%20taken%20hostage.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20offensive%20in%20Gaza%20has%20since%20killed%20more%20than%2013%20times%20that%20number%20of%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fhow-many-palestinians-have-died-gaza-war-how-will-counting-continue-2023-12-06%2F%5C%22%3E16%2C015%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Gaza%20health%20ministry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20direct%2